reviewText: This is a good size backpack, with lots of different compartments for holding just about anything you need. The material is pretty durable, and seems as though it would last a long time. On the outside, there is 3 different size zippered pockets, before you open up into the main compartment. I really like that this 3 pockets have their own isolated compartment, and don't lead into a secondary pocket. The first one is a small zipper pocket which would hold some small items. I think this zippered pouch would be great for holding a cell phone, and having easy quick access to it. Then there is another zippered pocket, which is slightly bigger, and could hold any miscellaneous items such as calculate, pens, pencils, etc. There is a third, larger compartment that is separate and independent of the first two. Once you open the large, main zippered compartment, it expands to hold books, notebooks, and any school related item. On the inside, there is also a separated, thicker pocket, where you could place a laptop or tablet. It is a padded sleeve, so it would protect your laptop or tablet from the books inside. I really like how expansive this backpack, and it really seems to have many uses (not just for school). I could see using this backpack for trips, work, hiking, etc. It holds quite a bit, and works well with kids and adult alike. I received this backpack at a discount in exchange for my honest review. Opinions are completely my own, and based on my own experience.

The backpack is made with quality and is very light weight. There are 6 overall compartments to the backpack. 2 large zippers for a laptop, binders and  notebooks, 1 small zipper pouch for a tablet, folders, two side pouches for holding water bottles and other necessities. And one last pouch in the front for holding your phone and other personal belongings.

The backpack fits my 17 inch laptop which is quite hefty, and it holds up very well. Inside the backpack there are little pockets for organization, so you can put pencils inside the pocket, kind of like a pencil pouch. There really is a lot of room and space for you to put things. I don't think my son has that many school supplies to even use all of the space. It's a great backpack for me to use personally, but even then I don't fill all of the compartments up. In the biggest zipper compartment there is a pocket designed for your laptop, which I like a lot because it keeps my laptop very secure in the backpack when I move around.

The design is nice, it looks very geometrical and sciencey. I feel it is a good unisex backpack for boys and girls. I think that the backpack would be great for college students who have a lot books, binders, and a laptop to hold. Overall great quality backpack, light weight, lots of compartments, and cute. I got the backpack for a discount, but came here to drop the honest truth.
summary: Great backpack lots of space, but still light weight, not just for kids, but for adults to use as well!

reviewText: Finding a good quality backpack thats made well AND reasonably affordable can be more of a challenge than one thinks. My daughter has a tendency to carry half the house in her backpack, so in order for a backpack to not fall apart it has to be well-made and it needs to hold quite a bit as well. This backpack is fantastic. I was really surprised at how large this bag actually is. I don't think the product pictures fully show how much will actually fit in this bag. It has one main large compartment, with a separate pouch for a laptop or tablet. It has padding to keep your laptop protected as well. There are several additional pockets on the exterior of the backpack. This leaves plenty of room for everything you need, and its also a lot easier to stay organized. She can keep all of her pens and pencils in a separate pouch and they won't end up broken in the bottom of her backpack. The small zippered pouch is the perfect size for her phone or Ipod too. This backpack is made of a durable, canvas type material, so its going to hold up very well over time. The colors, oh the colors. This backpack really is as vibrant and pretty in person as in the product pictures. My daughter absolutely loves the design and the colors. Overall, Im extremely pleased with this bag and the Cougera brand. I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.
summary: Fantastic Backpack!  The design is amazing and the bag is very well-made!

I LOVE THIS BAG!  It is exactly what I had been looking for ... well made, very functional, and it looks GREAT!

Love this bag. I am not a purse person but I've found myself taking it everywhere even if there's barely anything in it. It is smaller than I expected (the Amazon dimensions are slightly off - the dimensions in the description from the company are more accurate). My dimension are approximate but it's about 13 inches wide at the bottom, 11 inches wide at the top where it opens, 10 inches tall, 3 inches wide at the bottom and 2 inches wide at the top. I thought I could fit my MacBook Air in it based on the Amazon dimensions but the opening is not wide enough for it. However, it does fit plenty of stuff plus has big and small pockets to keep everything organized. The small front pockets are good for a Cliff bar, my keys, and lip gloss. The big front pocket can easily fit a Kindle. The back pocket is about the same size as the front. There's also an inside zipped pocket that can hold receipts, travel itineraries, and a small notebook. Opposite this pocket, there are two large open pockets that can hold a passport and five credit card pockets that can hold 3 or 4 cards in each one.

The only section that "locks" is the main compartment. There is a latch to lock the zipper on. It's pretty easy to lock and unlock. The zipper doesn't slide very smoothly so it can take some maneuvering which is a downside but not a huge hassle. There is also a flashlight and latch on the inside of the bag. The latch is great for hooking on a set of keys. I realized if I really need a second section that "locks", I can easily latch this hook onto the back zippered section. The little ribbon on it is long enough to do so. Granted, you can cut this ribbon easily with scissors but would still slow someone down if they are trying to get in that pocket.

The strap doesn't completely detach. Just one side of it is removable. The length of it can easily be adjusted and it ranges from about 28 to 50 inches in length. It has a locking mechanism on the side that detaches. It takes just a second to unlock this from the bag once you know how it unlatches. Seems somewhat easy for a thief to remove this part if they are familiar with this bag but otherwise it wouldn't be very easy. It took me some time to figure out how it worked so there's enough of a delay there to throw someone off. I also like that this strap can be looped around something then reattached. You can easily loop the strap around a chair or subway pole and then relatch it to help prevent someone from running off with it.

The wristlet is an added bonus. It fits the smaller iPhone 6, some cash, and a slim set of keys. There's a strap on it that can be detached or you can hook it on to something for added security when traveling.

Other than being a little small, it's a great buy with lots of cool features and some style to it as well!
summary: Great features, fits lots of stuff, and plenty of pockets!

First of all, this purse arrived faster than anticipated. The quality of it is outstanding, very durable but not too stiff. I love that it's a crossbody bag. The design of the purse with the zippers and pockets are great. What I love most was the ID pouch built into this purse! It eliminates the need for me to carry a wallet in the purse, making it more lightweight for my every day use. It also came with a wrist wallet. Also this purse has a tiny built in flash light on the side. I appreciate that this is an anti-theft purse and I love everything about it. This is one of the best purchases I've ever made from Amazon.

As mentioned, this IS a very sturdy, good looking bag. The deal breaker for me, however, for any handbag is the zipper: You have to hold the fabric end of it to zip it up. I am a lazy bones and need to have the zipper be a one-handed operation kind of thing. So, returned the bag. Also worth mentioning is that this bag, like some of this brand's bags, is very stiff. I'm sure with use it might loosen up but at this size, its a little like carrying around a briefcase. Too bad, the quilting is quite nice. Instead I got a different Travelon two pocket bag that has a zipper sewed onto the bag, and is less stiff.
summary: If you're okay with the zipper, great. If not, skip it.

Let me start by saying that I graduated with a Theatre degree, and I am a firm believer in dressing my mood for the day. I can go from preppy glamor to hard punk verging on goth to bohemian from one day to the next.

As soon as I saw these necklaces, I knew I needed to get them. I grew up in the 90s wearing these necklaces and this is exactly what I remember from almost 20 years ago. I was so excited when these came back in the style, however when I went to the store, they were at least five dollars per necklace. I could never justify spending that much for a nostalgic memory. I was very excited when I saw that I could get five necklaces for such an inexpensive amount.

My only complaint is that they are a little tight on my neck which makes it bulge slightly when nodding my neck, but I would much rather it be slightly tight than too big.

Overall, I would highly recommend these bracelets, especially at less that two dollars per necklace. I would highly recommend these to anyone looking to get the tattoo chokers.

The width seems like it could accommodate a wide range of folks.  Overall this is a very good item and would make a wonderful gift for any holiday.  I received this product for a discount rate in exchange for my honest review. This however has not influenced my opinion. As an online shopper I know how important these reviews are in helping someone decide whether or not to buy a product.  If this review was helpful please mark yes.

My dogs love to walk, rain or shine.  Me, I'm more of a shine gal myself.  But I thought maybe the Fenical Hooded Camouflage Raincoat/Poncho could help make those rainy days less gloomy.  Here's my two cents so far.

-Awesome color: I'm not sure this will really hide me in the woods, but this so cute I want to be noticed!
-Waterproof tested: Since we're having a drought, I tested this out with my lawn sprinkler (my neighbors must think I'm nuts).  My shoes got wet, but not my clothes.
-Decent fit:  I'm over 6 feet tall, so this only came to about my knees.  But that's still tons longer than my current raincoat.  The width seems like it could accommodate a wide range of folks.
-Interesting material: I have no idea what PU plaid with taffeta treatment is.  I can say it is much better than the cheap, throw-away plastic poncho I have.  Water really beads up well on this (see picture below) and then just rolls off.
-Multiple uses: I like that I could unsnap the sides of this and flatten it out for other uses, especially given the grommet corners.  I had been thinking about using it to line the bed of my SUV when hauling stuff to the dump, but this is just too pretty for that.  When you are done using, this comes with a matching storage bag too.
-Keeping it real: I got hot after wearing this for a few minutes (didn't seem the most breathable).  In fairness, it was 80 plus degrees out, so getting sweaty was probably inevitable.

I was thrilled to receive this product at a discount in exchange for an honest review, and I hope this is a helpful one too.  I take this seriously, since just like you, I look at reviews so I can made informed purchases.  My bottom line: the Fenical Hooded Camouflage Raincoat/Poncho is even cuter in person, and fought my sprinkler off like a champ.  Great purchase.
summary: Cute camo design almost has me hoping for rain!

reviewText:

The design is super cute, and the colors are identical to what shows in the picture.

This poncho is made out of a high-quality material that is quite durable.  It hasn't shown any signs of wear yet, and I don't think it will any time soon.  It won't snag on branches or anything like that while outside.  It's good quality.

As an unexpected bonus, I am actually able to fit this back into the carrying bag after use.  Things can never fit back into their carrying bags after use, so that's a plus!  Especially because I really only use this product when camping and a random shower pops up (as frequently happens in the south), I need this to take up as little space as possible among my camping gear.

reviewText:
The first thing I noticed about this faux leather bag is the beauty of the serenity blue color, reminiscent of glacial waters. The second thing I noticed was the lovely design of the bag. Small, compact, versatile, it may be used as either a crossover or shoulder bag, as the strap is adjustable. The metal hardware is tasteful, attractive, and appears to be durable. This bag is a perfect travel companion.

This bag is evenly and sturdily stitched and has a saffiano finish that will help make it resistant to scratches, as well as more durable and easy to clean. The interior of the bag is fully lined and has a pocket sleeve  that can accommodate one's smartphone or smartphone accessories. The interior also has five credit card sized sleeves that can accommodate identification and credit cards. There is an interior zippered compartment that is perfect for small items. This interior zipper is expertly set and zips open and shut easily. There is also a small key ring on the outside of this interior zippered compartment to which one may attach one's keys, which is a nice touch. The interior of the bag is relatively spacious for a small, compact bag.

The exterior of the bag has a slip in pouch on the front and back of the bag. Each pouch is suitable for carrying a paperback book or even a smartphone for easy access. My Kindle, when inserted vertically, fits quite nicely in either of these pouches, though for security purposes, I prefer using the back pouch for this purpose.

The Achilles heel in this bag, which I received from the seller in exchange for an impartial review, is the exterior zipper to the main compartment. Although it zips open and shut all the way, it is not done without a struggle, as the zipper seems to get stuck at various points. I can understand the complaints that others have had with this bag in regard this zipper breaking. Upon close examination of the bag, it is easy to see why. The zipper is clumsily set. It is not evenly set in the bag, with more grosgrain of the zipper backing showing at different intervals than others. So, it fails in its execution.

This is strictly a quality control issue. Once a zipper is unevenly set, as it is with this bag, the zipper will get stuck and, ultimately, break. The seller needs to ensure that the zipper backing be inset and sewn into the bag evenly, so that the entire zipper is at all points equidistant from the edge of the bag. Once the zipper is evenly inset  into the bag, the zipper will open and shut evenly. Were it not for this quality control issue,  This would be a five star bag.

reviewText:
I am so impressed and surprised by the quality and look of this top. It looks just like the picture, honestly, and that's so rare. It's also quite flattering despite not being fitted through the waist. Also, the lace across the top obscures enough for most ladies to wear this without a bra (assuming that's comfortable for them). The one drawback is that the lace is only in front so if you do choose to wear a bra it will show in the back. I will probably wear this with a tank underneath just because I'm not very comfortable without a bra.

All in all its a very sexy top yet also manages to seem demure because of the high neck and Victorian vibe. I'm 5'2" 160 pounds with a C chest and the Medium fit me very well (a bit tight in the shoulders but I have broad shoulders and its stretchy so it's all good). I will say that it's a bit short. It barely covers my waistband and I have a short torso. I imagine someone of a normal height might end up showing an inch or two of belly. If that isn't appealing it still looks great over a tank top.

EDIT: I ended up returning this top. It's still awesome but the first time I went to actually wear it out (not just try it on) I noticed a kind of black mark on the front... It was hidden within the folds, maybe something from packing? Anyway, just check all the folds of the fabric before you wear it, this was probably a one-off but still. Leaving the five stars because it is awesome and I might buy another one if I ever have a need for something like that again.

reviewText: Well done for my waist

I first ordered an XL as per the size chart in the description, since my waist is 34", but had to send it back because it was far too big and slipped down to my hips instead of sitting at my waist when wearing it. When I measured the waist of the XL when flat and unstretched, it was definitely larger than 27.3"! The "elastic" of the waistband is not really that stretchy, and I would say that the true flat measurement is much closer to the "B" measurement of the size chart.

After returning the XL, I ordered a L, and I am much happier with the fit of this size for me! It sits comfortably at my waist without slipping down or being too tight, and the thick fabric of the skirt itself is very comfortable and has the swing I was looking for. It's a little long for someone who's short (I'm 5'3" and it hits me just slightly above mid-calf), but that's an easy problem to solve. All in all, now that I have the right size, I'm very pleased with this find!
summary: Size chart is misleading, but skirt itself is great

reviewText:
This swimsuit is lovely! I don't wear bikinis, and its hard to find swimsuits that fit well.
Fit
Im 510, 145 pounds, and a 32D. I usually wear a 6, and ordered the 4/6 large. It fits, but its a tiny bit tight in the bum and across the back (where there is elastic). The top fits well and Im not falling out all over the place though, which is great!
The space between the cups on top and bikini lining is about eight inches. Some other reviewers have mentioned that they have tried it on and its bunched up in the torso, so I figured Id take a picture of just how much distance there is. (To see if that works for you, measure from the bottom of your bra to your hip bone)  It is not super full coverage in the bottom. (Please excuse how pasty I am!) In the picture I have included measuring the length of the bust to waist, you can see how there isn't a lot of difference between the seat of the suit and the crotch (front).
Construction/fabric
Its well constructed, there aren't any loose seams. The lining fabric is a little bit thin. You cant see anything because there is another layer over it, but after seeing how thin the fabric is, I am glad I got the navy instead of the white.
The bottom lining is sewn down completely, so you don't have to worry about it shifting, and the cups are well padded.
One thing to remember is that because it is a crochet style swimsuit it needs even more gentle care than a normal suit because it can snag on things. Normal swimsuits shouldnt be washed in the washer so they last longer, this I would even be really careful washing by hand in some sinks.

reviewText:
I am a huge fan of pendants. I am constantly wearing necklaces, I typically just choose a pendant and just keep it on for a week. I have been looking for ones with some color and flower looking ones and when I came across this one, I thought this might be really nice for work and everyday wear. This necklace came in a nice beautiful box. The pendant itself was smaller than I thought it would be, but it is beautiful. I like how it looks and it impressed me. I do want say this though that while part of this is sterling silver, I believe the rest of it is not. I mean it won't fade and give anyone a rash or anything, but the sterling alive 925 stamp isn't on the pendant itself but just on the part where it hangs off the necklace. Either way, it is still a very nice piece. The necklace chain itself is sterling though, I believe.

Overall, I would recommend this for anyone looking for an inexpensive, fun piece to wear to work or for causal purposes. It is nice and looks great!

reviewText:
Everything about this necklace, from the design to the box, exceeded my expectations.  When I saw the pendant on-line, I was a bit underwhelmed by the photos, but I decided to take a chance on it, anyway.  Im very glad I did!  The necklace arrived in a stunning gift box.  The case has a velvety burgundy-colored octagonal box, with a dark rose colored ribbed ribbon trim around the sides that is made into a box on the top of the box.  The necklace is attached to a card covered with the velvety material.  I will keep this box in my personal collection because it is so special.  If you're looking for a necklace that would make a good presentation as a gift, this one will fit the bill nicely.

The necklace chain is extremely eye-catching.  The twisted chain design catches the light as you move and makes the silver sparkle and shine.  The pendant is a little bigger than my thumb nail.  Since you don't know how big my thumbnail is, Ive provided a photo with the pendant next to a dime.  It is well-designed, and it is a quality piece of jewelry, not just another piece of costume jewelry.

In summary, I love this necklace, and Im glad to have it in my jewelry collection.

Do I recommend the product?  Yes, absolutely!
Would I buy the product again?  Yes.
Would I be willing to pay full price in the future?  Yes.

Disclosure:  I received this product at discount, in exchange for offering an honest review.  I am not affiliated with the products company in any way, and hope you find this review helpful.  If you have any questions, please let me know, and I will try to help you.

It's a good match with the pendant in terms of sparkle and proportion.  This looks much more expensive than it is. I also love the gift box this came in. It showcases the necklace beautifully and makes gift giving that much easier. I put a lot of stock in presentation and this one knocked it out of the ballpark!

reviewText:
Dave's wife:

First I have to say that these are great shorts. They're comfortable and I like the longer length (which is hard to find these days).

However, I do feel that they run a bit small. I'm a size 6 across the board, and the size 6 did fit but it was a bit uncomfortable for me. They buttoned and everything with no issue, but I just felt like they could have been cut a bit more relaxed through the leg.

I went up 1 size and they're perfect for me.

I'm a curvy 6, so that may have been the issue, but either way I felt like the 8 was perfect.

The pockets feel like a good size too, even though functional back pockets would have been nice.

I'd buy again.

-------UPDATED---------

It seems that these shorts get a bit bigger as you wear them, so I should have stuck with the size 6 (my true size). I ended up doing some minor alterations to take them in.

Also, these shorts actually have fully functional back pocket bags...for some reason they're just sewn closed. Just take out the stitch closing the pocket and *poof*- instant back pocket.

Also the hinge started to come undone, I had to use pliers to clamp it down. But it didn't break(yet, I hope it doesn't because I love it). Besides all of that soooo cute!
Its pretty but the Stone was not centered in the prongs then it fell off. To big to fit back in place. Bar is probably stainless but the rest feels like plastic.

Yet again, another septum clicker advertised as stainless steel but yet the clicker is only PLATED stainless steel. A complete waste of money. Too bad you cannot return body jewelry or I would have sent this back. For those of us with severe metal allergies, this plating, especially in the nose, will deteriorate very fast and is not worth it to have an artist put this in and then have to take it out a few months later. False advertising and I am writing reviews on sellers that are doing this.
summary: Clicker is stainless steel PLATING, not fully stainless steel. Cheaply made. Do not buy.

reviewText:
I love red and when Fashion Land offered to let me test out this scarf I jumped at the chance to wear this beautiful fashion accessory.  The red color and the design is what drew me to it.  It is a show stopper.

When I opened the box I was struck by the beautiful presentation.  The scarf is in a lovely red box.  Inside theres an added surprise of a Chinese Knot and a gift box for it.  Ive used these before to hang off dresser pulls, doors and you can even put them on a Christmas tree.  Many uses for them.  The scarf is wrapped in tissue.  Also included is a pretty red gift bag.

The scarf is 100% silk and is very soft and supple.  I loved the feel of it.  It is super long.  I can wrap this several times around my neck.  A brochure is enclosed to show you different ways to wear the scarf.  It is also unisex so men and women can wear it.

Instructions say to dry clean or wash by hand.  Use a medium temperature iron.  As far as I can tell it looks well made.

This is a beautiful accessory that youd be proud to wear out to dinner, to the theater or any event. FYI:  In my photo I didn't try to style the scarf.  I wanted to let you see the beautiful design and length.

I received this free for my unbiased and honest opinion.

FYI:  Modern Usage of Artistic Knots

Along with being symbolic gifts or messages, knots are still used if they wear traditional Chinese clothing or as good luck charms. They are a means of fastening traditional garments instead of buttons or wooden pegs. Now, silk is most widely used to make these clothing knots.
They are used as jewelry such as even rings, earrings, bracelets, and necklaces. They are sold as handicraft novelty items too.

http://www.chinahighlights.com/travelguide/culture/knot.htm

So disappointing this was, I was looking for a chunkier, thicker SS(Stainless steel) bracelet as I have plenty of midrange size ones and the second it came out of the package I knew I was not looking at a 20MM bracelet, in fact it measured exactly at 16MM, the clasp being 18MM. I had a friend over who had just picked up a 20MM SS bracelet at a local shop for himself and wow it dwarfed mine and felt like real high quality SS. The SS in mine feels cheap, it doesn't have the right sound to it that other SS have when you shake it in your hand(anyone familiar with SS will know what I mean). All in all a bad deal, to make matters worse it came from Germany, not like I'm going to attempt to return it!!

Beware of vendor's origins on Amazon because I had no idea my item would be coming from another continent or I would never have ordered it because returns are impossible and more trouble than they're worth. I tried to photograph it but it seemed I needed another hand as I couldn't quite get the exact tight measurement and there is a slight shadow to it, but it's visible enough. 4MM is a lot to lose, I bet their 26MM item is likely 20MM.
I don't take pleasure in leaving such a negative review, but this needed a heads up to the public. Too often I receive inferior products online and do nothing about it.
summary: Wrong measurements, cheap materials and shipped from Germany so I'm stuck with it.

I ordered this ring to wear with my wedding band and engagement ring because I prefer stacking my rings. This ring was delivered very quickly and it came in a very beautiful jewelry box. The cubic zirconia on the ring are very shiny and clear looking - next to my actual diamonds they look very nice and I'm sure the ring looks more expensive than it really is!

The only issues I had with this ring were that it becomes slightly misshapen when you resize it and the portion of the ring that you slide inwards or outwards to make it bigger/smaller can actually irritate your skin if you don't squeeze/smash it down back into place once you have resized it. I strongly recommend you size this ring only once or twice and just wear it on one particular finger. I don't think it is really durable enough to continually pull and move around too many times.

Other than that I am very satisfied with this ring and I have already gotten several compliments on it.
summary: Great little stacking ring. Re-sizable for any finger.

reviewText:
I received this ring in a lovely red and black box - very nice for Valentine's Day! The ring itself is pretty, but less so than the picture. Specifically, the band is not as shiny as it is in the picture. The cz is very pretty though. The picture definitely does it justice. The ability to adjust the band is a selling point. However, if you need to adjust the ring significantly, to say, a size 10 like myself, it warps the shape of the band considerably. I love that the adjustment function is kind of hidden, it makes it a lot more comfortable than rings with similar functions. However, in the case of needing to adjust it significantly from it's standard size, it leaves the exposed band quite tarnished. It is my opinion that the ring would be more appealing if it came in different sizes rather than a one-size-fits-all type of thing. Overall though, I'm quite happy with my purchase.

When I saw this ring I couldn't stop thinking about it.  I was able to purchase this item at a discount, so I knew I had to try it. I love the way the flowers look---it's right up my alley!  I love the idea of a "hidden" adjustable ring, unfortunately the finger I purchased this item for is a large finger (my middle finger).  My ring finger is a size 7 so I'd say by middle finger is possibly a 9 or 10.  The adjustable part of the ring pointed up and bothered my finger.  Tomorrow I'm going to try and press it down to see if it will fit comfortably.  I think people with smaller fingers, size 6 and under would probably like this ring a lot.  It felt study while in it's smallest setting---even when I made it a bit bigger. For those of you with larger fingers, this may not be the ring for you as it's not as sturdy the larger you make the ring. Over all I'm excited to show off the flower part of the ring, but not too excited about the adjustable part. If not, I know my daughter will love this ring.
summary: I love the way the flowers look---it's right up my alley

I don't want to get my ring resized because when I finish nursing the girls I will lose the weight quickly as I did with my other child. I still want to wear a ring though. It's very sparkly AND it's adjustable! I LOVE that it's adjustable because I can wear this even while I'm losing weight and I can just squeeze it tighter until my actual wedding ring fits again. This is very high quality. When I was extending it to try it on I accidentally pulled too hard and I pulled it open completely. My heart sank because I was sure it would break when I closed it back again but to my happy surprise the ring was fine... This really is a lovely little ring, no matter what you use it for. I am so happy to have a ring I can wear that will grow and shrink with me as I embark on my mom adventure.
I received this item at a promotional rate. My review is 100% my honest experience using this product.

I was surprised when I opened this product. The box is substantial and sturdy. Not what I expected at all. And the ring itself is gorgeous. The stones are shiny and look like a diamond. The quality is superior. It is very well made. You could not find this quality of a ring in any of the major department stores. Especially not for the price. This is a beautiful product, at a great price, that will not disappoint when you open it.
I received a discount for reviewing this product. It did not influence the review. This ring is very pretty.

This ring is beautiful! You would never guess that it is not a "thousands of dollars" ring. My mom had lost her wedding ring years ago and my dad said he would never buy her another ring, so she has always just wore her promise ring. I came across this ring and thought it would be perfect for her! Since I didn't know what size her finger was, this ring was perfect since its adjustable. It also comes in a cute little box. She was very excited and is now looking for a little wedding band that you could wear along with it. I will update my review after awhile to see how well the ring holds up.

Its ok. Honestly when it was posted such high ratings, i was thrilled due to the price.
Its a nice jacket. Its a soft feeling jacket. The only thing that i didn't like is that is was soooo light.
Honestly, that day i received a few packages in the mail. There were 3 boxes, all medium sized (under 24"). I was thinking that the larger and heavier box was the jacket. I was kind of baffled when i opened it and it was something else.  The jacket was in a plastic bag and was light as a bird (well like a crow, maaaybe? - or similar). Im used to leather jackets being kinda heavy weighted and thick.
Its soft and says 100% REAL LEATHER, BUT actually, if there wasn't any tags, i would have thought it was PLEATHER or PU LEATHER.
Just be careful because it feels like it will rip easily (easier than the thick and heavy leather jackets).
Thats what i was looking for. Guess i should have checked the weight of the product first. My husband wants to keep it because it was a gift or else i would have returned it and got another one from a different seller.
Kind of bummed. But i learned a good lesson.... If its too good to be true, well it probably is....

I was looking forward to this product, but I have both a positive and negative critique on it. I will commence with the positive followed by the negative.
Overall the sizing for the body portion was amazing. It fits around my midsection and is actually long enough. Items like this have a tendency of running short for me so I was pleasantly surprised. The lace appears to be a respectable quality, there are no loose strings visible, it had a nice stretch to it and the shiny gold thread is well done. I like that the straps tie around your neck so it would be easily adjustable.
I have two negative things to say about the product, and to me they are large subjects.
The foremost being, there were no product tags attached. This makes the item feel used to me and I am not comfortable with that. The tags weren't even included in the package. I found this extremely odd considering the item photos clearly show tags. The second issue I have is the fit of the top. The photos have a rather busty woman modeling the top therefor I was convinced about the fit while purchasing. I am a large C cup and this didn't even come up to my nipples. I measured and the lace portion of the top is 4 inches tall. I would highly recommend you measure your body or bra to insure this will fit your chest. There is no way I could wear this item if I wanted it to cover my breasts even a little.
My overall opinion is that it would be a wonderful purchase for a smaller busted individual or someone who measures and is happy with where it will sit on their body. For me, the bottom of my nipples and feeling the item as used just wasn't cutting it. I will be looking into a return since I am unaware of the return policy of garmets such as this.
summary: Good quality- questionable lace sizing- no new item tags- nice fit bottom portion

reviewText: They were very comfortable but too small and shrunk more in washing.

I received these socks as a complimentary gift for offering feedback on other socks I bought from Vero Monte.  The high quality of both sock sets that I got was undeniable.  These socks form to the shape of my foot as well as any socks I've ever had.  As someone whose feet generally overheat and sweat, I appreciated how light and breathable these socks were.  I also really like the height of the sock, not too low or high, so it works fine with wearing pants.  Given how well it molds to my foot/ankle, it also doesn't shift while wearing.  It's a pretty perfect sock.

I'm so thoroughly impressed with the great customer service of this fine American company.  They reached out to me in a very personal manner; that makes me just want to root for their success.  I'm making a purchase now of some more socks, of course not just because of my high regard for Vero Monte, but of the great socks I expect to receive.

Love the look on these leggings! Fits perfectly.

I really love the loo of these leggings. They are flattering, and I love the design. You can see from the pics that they are mesh on the front of the leg below the knee, on the back, and a bit up the outer thigh. The other fabric is a spandex/lycra, with a bit of sheen. The leggings are not thick, but not see through, either, so they're perfect to wear for a long workout or even on a warmer day when you don't feel like wearing capris or shorts. They are high waisted, which is nice, and the waistband is wide so it does not twist or fold. My only problem with these is that they are quite large! I am 5'8" 130lbs so I usually fit between a S and a M. I figured I would size up just in case on these, that that was the wrong decision. I definitely should have ordered a S or maybe even XS. As you can see from the pics they are not super form fitting, but they still look cute.

PROS
great design, good material, nice high waist

CONS
way too big! order at least a size down

*I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest review

These are pretty cute shorts, but they do run just a tad small. I am 5 foot tall and weigh about 115 pounds. I usually wear a size small, 26, or 2 in bottoms. I ordered a size medium just in case they ran small. Also, sometimes it's better to go a size up rather than a size down. I'd rather it be baggy than too tight. These were tight in the waist and just barely loose in the butt and thighs. When I say thighs though, they barely cover your butt. I am not into my butt hanging out, but it is hard to find shorts these days that are not completely revealing. These are high waisted as well. They zip up in the back and tie in a cute bow in the front. They are just not for me though. They appear to be classy shorts, but once I got them they were too short to be classy in. If I went another size up, it would just be too big in the waist. BUT, these will be very cute on someone who does not mind wearing booty shorts.
Also, the fabric seems to be made pretty well. Not as flimsy as I have seen some.
If you look at the pictures you can tell where the back seam ends and how much material is left to cover your legs (like an inch or two).

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I hope this helps when considering purchasing these shorts.
summary: Cute highwaisted shorts, but a little too short for me.

reviewText: I did a lot of research before spending the money on a kitchenette for my 19 month old. I wanted it to be something that would last for years to come. I am glad I chose this kitchenette because it's not only adorable but its perfect size for my daughter. She spends so much time washing her veggies and cooking up new things. It is very functional with storage on the bottom but yet cute with the fake window. I was skeptical because it's white but I've had it for over two months now and still looks brand new. Overall I gave four stars because my daughter did break off the little pink napkin holder and the microwave door came off. The napkin holder was an easy fix with some glue but haven't attempted to fix the microwave door yet. Also if you do not have the patience to read directions or a second pair of hands to help with assemble I would think twice. There was a lot of pieces to put together. I like build things, so for me it wasn't a big deal but I can see how others might get overwhelmed.

Unfortunately like other reviews my kitchen has some defects. Overall exactly what I want in a kitchen but the main piece that the sink sits in has a chunk missing out of it and the two pink knobs for the stove were broken. I contacted seller for replacement parts but they are not available disappointed that a toy I just purchased and assembled is damaged with no resolution, buyers beware.

While assembly was fairly easy, there were multiple issues. The two top nobs had been broken off and still obviously placed inside the box together. It wad obvious that they were broken as they both had jagged plastic on the bottom and you could see the other half of the plastic in the corresponding holes. Next, 2 holes had to be drilled myself as the holes it came with were off so far i couldn't make them work. Next, the slotted pink shelves on the upper unit, the whole thing was drilled so off square it really strands out how crooked out looks. Lastly, the pink little box that goes on the back wall wad totally split at the seems and i had to use superglue and a clamp to make it work.

This assembly was much more difficult than it should have been and the QC process obviously failed on my box. If it wasn't Christmas weekend when i put this together for my kid, the day before Christmas eve in fact, I'd return this for another. I had to MacGyver this thing together at enough places that i can't recommend it for most folks, not everyone could do it.

After owning a KidKraft Kitchen (my Jack Russell ruined with tinkle) I purchased this because I didn't want to spend a lot of $ for I have only one grandchild left (at present) that is young enough.  It arrived in a real FLIMSY box and parts were broken but I got some wood glue and a clamp and got through it.  The directions STINK!  Was really difficult but once complete it was cute but not as tall or as well made as the KidKraft I had owned before.  I would NOT recommend this product to anyone. Waste of $ & Time!

Parts started falling off after we took it apart. The kiddos love it but kinda sad after spending 5hrs putting it together to see parts of it right as kiddo opened the mice wave door it snap. Kiddo is 3 years old and not the hulk :(

reviewText: I had hoped the material would have been less like a tee shirt material.  It's very thin, but stretchy - no idea if I'd say it's cotton, but it's like a thin tee shirt and will show every lump and bump if it's too tight on the person.  I live in South Florida, so it will be comfortable all year long. And that's the only reason it's ok for me.  Luckily I ordered the x-large because the reviews say it runs small.  I'm only 5 ft. tall with measurements of 37 Bust, 33 Waist, 41 Hips.  The x-large actually fits good, except for the sleeves which come to the bottom of my fingertips.  They are described as being 3/4 length sleeves, so the fit of the sleeve length is off,  However, the the upper part of the sleeve has a little elastic so that when my arms are bent, the sleeves can be pulled up a little.  But some people like having long sleeves.  Just don't expect them to be 3/4 unless you're a tall person.  As for the length of the entire garment, it covers my bottom and will be ok with either leggings or regular pants.  I'm somewhat disappointed that the color is actually more of a soft green than bluish aqua.

reviewText:
So...when I ordered this item, they sent me the shirt but the WuTang logo was upside down.  I was thankful to get a message from customer service stating that they would send out a new one immediately, at no additional cost to me.  However, the second one that has arrived is totally different from the first one.  The second shirt does have the logo correct, however the material is totally different, and it is greatly oversized.

The first shirt is 57% cotton/ 5% spandex / 38% polyester.
The second shirt is 100% cotton and very stiff.

 Even the label on the shirts is different, indicating different manufacturers.  My wife pointed out that the first one appears to be a woman's tank top (based on how the back of it is shaped) and the second one (larger one) is a men's tank top.

I guess you never know what you're going to get if you order one of these.  Customer service is great, and willing to replace the defective items, but at this point, I'm not sure what I want...I live the material of the first one, but it's a woman's style tank....if they can give me the men's version in this material, I'd be happy.
summary: You never know what you're going to get from them!

reviewText:
Beautiful so very very pretty.  I can't believe how lovely these earrings are at for the price.  Great quality.  I love anything that sparkles like glitter and these sparkle just like they do in the picture.  So very light you don't know that you are wearing them.  I have fallen asleep in these ever since I put them on.  They come with that tiny silicone backing so the posts don't poke your neck.  They are strong and do not bend easily.  They are designed so that it looks like the bottom globe looks like it is hovering under the other one.  So unique.  It is worth the long wait for shipping.  I received them three weeks before the shipping said it would arrive.  So I believe it took about  3 weeks.  I just love looking at them I recommend these for any princess in your life.  Not for a tom boy.  Very simple and so attractive.  People will notice you because of these earrings.
I did receive a discount in exchange for my honest review. Please understand I received a discount only I did not receive money. I did not get paid to leave this review. Thank you and I hope I helped you with your decision!

These are great. Like 2 sets of earrings in one. I wear just the studs most of the time and on date nights add the other part to change to an evening look. Great locking back so not to lose them. Got theses free or a discounted price.

I received these earrings literally a month early! I was very excited for that.
Upon receiving they were in a little black pouch. The earrings come in 4 pieces total. One part of the earring that goes through the front, then the back part which is a hook like that attaches in the back. Then you take the rubber stopper and put it behind the loop in the back to hold it all in place.
They are comfortable and very sparkly! I wore these almost every day since I received them. I love them. I love that they are simple yet gorgeous and elegant. You can wear them to dress up, or even to dress down. I personally wore them both ways and they looked great both casual and dressy. At first I was trying to figure out how to put them on then once I figured out you need that rubber stopper I was okay. The rubber stopper holds them in your ears, otherwise they fall out.
They are not heavy and are very light on your ear lobe. They look gorgeous on and no matter what you are wearing someone is going to notice because of how sparkly and different they are. I love earrings and these are now my absolute favorite.
I received these earrings at a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased review of the earrings.

Edit after 10 days:  The earrings are literally falling out of my ears, it's like the "back" no longer holds onto the front part of the earring.  I've tried squeesing the sides together to get a tighter fit, but it's not working.  So I guess I just figured out what the extra backs were for.

These are my new favorite earrings because they are just as beautiful as I was hoping!  The dual crystal balls are so intriguing that they've already garnered me a compliment on how pretty they are.  The "backs" are actually attached to the lower ball which makes them very convenient because I was thinking that I would have to deal with 3 separate pieces.

These come with 2 extra backs though; one plastic and one tiny metal back.  I'm not entirely sure why you only get one of each, but it doesn't really matter to me since I'm hoping I won't need them anyway.

All in all these are so sparkly and pretty that you will not regret having these in your collection.  And even though I received a discount I will gladly buy more earrings from this seller because they have provided a beautiful product to me.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for a review that is truthful and unbiased, which I have done. If my experience with the product changes in an unreasonable measure I will update my review.

reviewText:
Wow, Wow, Wow!!  As a reviewer for Amazon, I have approximately 70-100 products come through my door in any given month.  It takes a lot to impress me at this point, but this scarf was certainly very, very impressive.  I couldn't believe how nicely it was packaged and all of the extras that came with it.  The scarf itself arrived in a nice, large ziplock-esque type bag.  Inside the bag was the scarf, as well as so much more.  They provided you with a beautiful red gift box in case you wanted to gift the scarf, an amazing quality, sparkly and shiny red gift bag with quality handles, as well as a Chinese knotted book mark and charm.  The charm and book mark also came with a high quality gift box.  It was all so beautiful, I was truly surprised and impressed.

The scarf itself is very soft and supple.  It has very rich colors and is very comfortable to wear.  It looks fantastic with a white oxford and business suit, and looks equally awesome with a slouchy black sweater and skinny jeans.  Very versatile.  I was seriously impressed with this product.

I received this product for free in exchange for my honest review and opinion, and that is what you get. Just like you, I rely heavily on these reviews before making a purchase, and I want to provide a helpful and honest opinion. If this review helped you, please give me a thumbs up, as that helps me!

purchased mine on eBay for $3.60. Looks an awful lot like a popular Tag Heuer model. Wasn't expecting much. Got more than i expected.

The negatives first: There are 3 lies on the dial, and one truth. The 1st lie is "Water Resistant 200 meters". The fact is this watch isn't even a little bit water resistant. Water seeps in around the crystal and there are no rubber gaskets in the crown nor in the pry-off back. The 2nd lie is "JAPAN MOVT". The movement is Chinese (of course) and is marked as such.  The 3rd lie is that the hands have white paint on them. They are not luminous at all. The truth is in the name. You want a Soki watch, that is what you get, a sucky watch.

Now here are the positives: This watch is really beautiful. The crystal appears to be glass and has a nice bevel around the edge. The Arabic numerals are raised and look as though they were either painted on or applied. The case is black and sturdy, with a protective notch for the crown. The 22mm strap is a leathery-looking synthetic material that stretches somewhat and is really comfortable, like a pair of crocs. Despite not being luminous, the white hands are easy to see in low light because of the contrast against the black dial. The watch disassembles easily, so even if you get some humidity inside the case, you can easily take it apart and dry it out. The movement, like most quartz movements, keeps time accurately. What more can you ask for from a cheap watch? It looks good and keeps time.

This review is for I&S Men's 12 Pack Low Cut No Show Ankle Socks - Size 10-13.

The value for these socks is great but I found them pretty thin and I wouldn't really call them low cut, I'd call them normal cut. reviewText:
I got these for my adult son who only wears no show or low cut socks. When the package arrived and I gave him the socks to check out, he immediately didn't like them. He said they were way too thin and polyester, not cotton. He almost didn't try them at all. He took them home and texted me later that night telling me everything he said about the socks was wrong. He said they were incredibly comfortable (and he has size 13-14 feet), stretched great, and, although thin, protected his feet and, as promised, didn't show over his trainers.

The socks come 12 pairs to  a set for a very good retail price. They are made of 98% polyester and 2% Spandex. My son still would prefer cotton as they absorb perspiration better but these socks also seem to be fairly absorbent as well. They also don't shrink a lot when washed and dried. They aren't good for cold weather but fine for moderate to hot weather and for the gym anytime.

The one thing that would make them perfect is if they had some cotton for better absorption but, in all, these are very comfortable, well fitting socks and they are a good value as well.

Please note that I paid a discounted price for these socks in exchange for my evaluation and honest review. I not affiliated with the seller nor was I compensated in any way for my review. I am a real Amazon shopper who buys lots of things for full price and some for discounted ones. I base all my reviews on the same things - quality, value, personal experience, and preference. These socks are well fitting, comfortable, and a great value.
summary: Socks that stretch for a perfect fit. My son loves them.

I bought these for my boyfriend and I. Mainly because he loves dragon's and prefers to only wear silver. The dragon is definitely bigger than the Phoenix so you can tell which is which. My boyfriend put his on first and asked if I was sure it was for guys. He wears about a size 13 ring and this was small, both in size and style. For him to wear it on his ring finger, the back of the ring had to be separated completely. I tried to pull mine to make it bigger but I couldn't budge it. He had to make it larger for me so I could wear it. I was about a size 8 on my ring finger and it works well. Sometimes it seems loose so I tighten it while it's on, but then have trouble taking it back off. The cubic Zirconia pieces are still in place. Those little pieces often fall off first. I wear mine on my ring finger mainly, my boyfriends taking to wearing his on his pinkie because he likes how it looks and almost finds it funny to have a ring there. Atleast for the Phoenix, the adjustable pieces slide together in the back so it's a smooth back, not like those ones from childhood that have two rough edges (like the color changer cheapo rings). I can't check the dragon because my boyfriend has it on and he isn't here but I would assume it's the same way. Sometimes I catch the top of my ring on things but I haven't snagged anything yet.

I received these for a discounted price for my fair and unbiased review of the product. I do not guarantee a 5 star rating in exchange for the discount.

the set of rings are pretty. They are buffed out and shiny, just like in the pictures. The lower areas, are more of a matte, or dull type of surface, which is good as it brings out the details of the ring much better. One thing that is misleading by the picture is the stone. On the picture, it shows the stone to be very clear, and shiny, where in person, it has more of a dull look to the stone. This was common for both rings, but more on the men's dragon, then then women's phoenix ring. The Woman's one, is a bit clearer then the men's.

This does have a Cubic Zirconia stone in it, as stated in the listing, but I have seen other Cubic Zirconia stones that were much clearer then these. So it is not because of the type of stone that they are not really shiny or clear. This is just a quality of a stone, or the cut of it, thing. This does in no way make it a poor ring, as you have to remember, these are not large stones, so it does not bring much attention to this fact when wearing it. The men's ring, with it being the largest of the stones, is only around an 1/8" in diameter, maybe a hair more. Also, the way that the stone is set in the men's ring, is slightly off from the picture too., I have included a picture so you can see how mine looks with the setting of the stone.

Since they are made out of silver, they are easy to bend too. If you look closely at the back of the band, you can see that these are made so that you can slide the band, or stretch it, by yourself, to make it the size that you need to fit you. This is good because you will not have to pay a jeweler to size the ring to fit you, which saves on cost. Just be careful not to over bend or kink it when adjusting it to the size that you need. after all, Like I said, it is made out of pure 925 silver, it is not just a coating of it, so it can bends somewhat easily,

On the sizing factor, it goes up to a pretty large size. I have larger hands. I wear an extra large in a men's glove, so that should tell you something about the size of my hands. And I had no problem with the dragon ring fitting my ring finger.

They came in a nice ring case too, not some kind of cheap bag or anything like that.

Overall, they are very pretty rings and I am very happy with them.

I did get these are a discount for giving a review. as for my rating, I dropped one star off, only because of the men's ring stone not being as clear as they show, or indicate that it is, in the listing. after all there is no clarity rating on them. The picture in the listing should be of the actual quality of the product that you get, where in this case, it pretty much is of everything but the stone. This does not make it a bad ring though, and it does not make me like it any less. You should just know what you are getting, and the picture here, is misleading. so -1 for that.

also, sorry for the pictures being a little out of focus, The glare from the rings was knocking the auto focus feature out of wack when trying to get the picture.

Positioned side by side. Beautiful presentation. These are quite neat. They are adjustable on the bottom of the rings. These rings you can slide the piece in and out per size needed. I wear a size 7 and my husband a size 11. I had no problems adjusting them for the sizes I needed. I retain water and I am also diabetic and my fingers often swell. These are great for me because of the ability to adjust. The womans ring has a beautiful heart with the word forever and the mens ring the shape is square and the word forever.  These can be used for any occasion. They can be used as an engagement ring, valentines or just a simple thinking of you. I also think they could  be used as a gift perhaps from mother to daughter. There are several possibilities and occasions these could be used. These rings are 925 sterling silver so I don't worry with my fingers turning green. This is a great metal and a good quality ring. This would be
 great for someone who doesn't have a lot to spend on a good quality ring or maybe your saving up for that one special ring. Remember this can indeed be adjusted and used on any finger. reviewText:
I bought these rings as an anniversary gift for my boyfriend. When they arrived, I saw they had come in a really pretty jewelry box. They were tucked safely inside, side-by-side, looking shiny and beautiful. The rings are a lot daintier than I expected, but the men's ring is still masculine. I gave the box to my boyfriend with a letter stating that I promised to love him forever, as stated on the ring. It was my promise to him. He loved his ring and put it on immediately, then made the same promise to me. Very happy with my purchase. Some of our friends immediately thought we got engaged, but we set them straight. However, that just goes to show that these rings can also be used for engagements if you're looking for something simple, elegant, and inexpensive. It also helps the the rings are adjustable. Beautiful jewelry. I highly recommend these rings.

I received these promise rings at a discount in exchange for an honest, unbiased review.

reviewText: 5days. The man's ring lose the dimond

Tyzon 925 Sterling Silver Promise Ring Luxury Design Cubic Zirconia for Couple Engagement This is a beautiful set of rings crafted of fine sterling silver. I very much enjoy that the rings are nickel free because I don't have to worry about our fingers breaking out, or allergic reactions. The rings are a lovely matched set with the man's ring having a single solitaire stone and the woman's ring having a center stone surrounded by 6 smaller stones on each side of the solitaire. The bands are adjustable as you can see if you look carefully at the back of the band in the picture. The inside back of both rings just slides to a larger size, as needed. I am sure you could take it to a jeweler and permanently set it to your correct size. The rings are beautifully crafted and smooth polished to perfection. I am enjoying the set of rings very much and my boyfriend loves his too. I love the shape and flow of this ring and the nice modern look of the set. I get complemented on it often and and happy because of it being crafted of noble sterling silver, it should last for a lifetime. I have no complaints or problems at all with this product and it's working well for me.

This ring is SO SIMPLE, and SO ELEGANT at the same time. I love it! The ring itself is adjustable, and it comes with 2, man and womans. The man ring only has 1 stud, so if you really wanted it to, it could pass for a womans ring. The ring was easy to fit to my finger, and it doesnt move or get caught on anything like most adjustable things do. Most of the time I expect inexpensive rings to rust or turn green when wet, I have tried to keep this one out of water, but just last nightI left it by the sink and my husband washed his hands after me and left water everywhere but no rust! I was so surprised that I tested it this morning and washed my hands with it, and no green finger! This is most definitely a great buy for the money.

Disclaimer: I purchased this ring for a free/discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

I love this Light Blue Aqaumarine color. Since the crystal is transparent it looks a little darker Blue toward the top and lighter Blue toward the wider bottom part. I love that effect. These drops are actually Swarovski Elements Pear shaped pendants. They are 22 X 13 mm. They have a hole at the top which is how they connect to the metal of the earring. This is a good design because that lets the crystal swing and move around. I like the medium length of these earrings. They are about 1.6 inches from top to bottom. I did not find them heavy at all and they are comfortable to wear. The ear hook in a straight line gives these earrings a clean and elegant look. I also like how they added those little clear crystals along the hook. Those add extra shine. These are easy to put on just by sliding into the ear. Since the back piece is long they stay on my ears and have not slipped out. *Tip: I recommend not pulling open these hooks and then pressing them tighter once you have them on your ears. Eventually that will weaken the metal along the top and they might break. Adjust the hook part to a comfortable width where you can put them on and where they won't be too open in the back once you have them on. Then just leave them like that. The metal is Sterling Silver and I did find the 925 stamp on the back of the earring hook. They are also Rhodium Plated which helps keep the Silver from tarnishing and protects it. These came with a small silver polishing cloth and a Pink velvet pouch and a gift box. Also included is a little Swarovski Elements hang tag to prove authenticity. Love the design and they look beautiful. These are as described and I did not find any flaws. I highly recommend these earrings. *****DISCLOSURE: I received this item free of charge to evaluate and review. All opinions are my own.

reviewText: What a lovely shirt. Ordering Asian sizes can be tricky, I ordered a US size 6/8, which is the smallest size offered and the shirt fits just like a size Medium, not too tight, perfect length and the sleeves are the right lengths too. The fabric is very light and comfortable and just so you know slightly see through. I like the design very much, it's simple and classic and can work with a variety of outfits. For the price, it's a great deal. Quality seems good too, all the stitching and buttons are correct and even. The seller was prompt and courteous and very friendly. The shirt came earlier than the estimated delivery date (and that's all the way from China, which is impressive), was packed well, came out of the package ready to be worn. It even has tags, in English, which is something some clothes from China do not. For reference in the photos...height 5'4", chest 34", hips 29". Hope this review helps you. reviewText: I bought them for my girlfriend and her daughter. These type of walets have always worked well for me.

I now carry 2 of these in my purse at all times...one for my credit and debit cards and one for my multiple store discount and club cards. The cases are really well made and hold a ton of cards without any issues shutting tightly. The hard case also makes me feel secure that if anything spills in my purse (it happens) the contents will be safely clean inside. I also like the fact that they are RFID safe. I am not really sure how you check the quality of this feature but to say that my identity and credit card numbers have not been stolen so I can only assume that the RFID is working properly. The cases come in a variety of colors and patterns that work for men and women while being stylish and fun to carry around. Sometime I only carry this wallet when I am going out for a night on the town and I get many compliments on how cute an compact it is.

summary: A stylish and secure way to carry your cards

reviewText:
I was a bit surprised one day when I went into a store I frequent. This store has a special card that accumulates points like so many stores have now. I have a small leather pouch that I keep my different cards in. I said to the gentleman that was helping me, let me get my card. He said no it's okay and asked for my little pouch. Knowing this person it didn't bother me to give him the whole pouch of cards. He took it, swiped the whole thing under the machine and it found and read the exact card he needed right through the stack of cards surrounding it. Like I said I was a bit surprised, but definitely not shocked. With all the technology increasing each and every day it wouldn't surprise me if in the near future a device is developed that will be able to bypass the RFID cases but in the meantime may as well take advantage of a case like this. I have heard before that some of RFID blocking cases actually only claim they work, when they don't. I wanted to get a chance to go to the store I mentioned and ask them to try one on their machine to see if these really do work. I don't have doubts in them, it's mostly to satisfy my curiosity. When I go back in there I plan on having them try. Until then, I will be assuming that they do. If they don't function as they should, I will come back and post an update. This set of cases contains six holders, each with a different design. They open and close very easily but not so easy that a case would fall open. The inside of these cases are all black and have eight slots for cards. You can add a few extra cards, if need be. These cases are durable and well made, I love all the different designs. I am very pleased with this purchase and as for the cost of this product you definitely can't go wrong in purchasing them. These days we need all the help we can get when it comes to protecting our personal information.
I received this set of cases at a discounted price for my honest review. I assure you that every product I review, whether I pay full price or a reduced price will get an honest review. I take my reviews serious because I know people count on an unbiased opinion of a product. As a consumer myself I look to these reviews to receive more information about a product I am considering purchasing. Buying something sight unseen makes honest reviews even more important.
summary: Keeping personal information is more than important.

reviewText:
As explained by the seller, Bundle Monster, these wallets help with your protections from identity theft.  As we all know it is an ongoing problem and a growing problem, we should all be safer with our identity.  I believe this is a great first step.  There are card readers that people can use to get close to you and steal your information, but with this wallet, you can safely put your cards inside.  You can fit multiple cards in this wallet, and it has enough storage for 8 separate compartments (you can put more than one card in each compartment.  The designs on the wallets are pretty nice (I'm not much into skulls, but I thought about giving that one away).  Overall, they are very well made and fit into my back pocket nicely.  I would definitely recommend this product to family, friends, and anyone who cares about their identity.  Plus, you get 6 wallets for one great price... how can you pass up such a great deal?
I did receive this product at a discount in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.  All opinions are my own.  I rely on other reviews on Amazon when I purchase any item, and would not give false information.
summary: I believe this is a great first step

I ordered this bathing suit in a size large, which is the largest size available in this listing; I usually wear between a medium and a large in women's clothing.  According to the sizing chart listed in the product description, this should have fit, but unfortunately that was not the case.  This bathing suit was at best a size medium and I couldn't get it on at all, so I passed it on to my niece, who wears between a size small and a medium and it fit  her very well.  The quality of the overall bathing suit is great, so I only took off one star for the sizing issue.

I do like the unique styling of the shoulders of this bathing suit.  The strings are easy to adjust to allow you to wear this bathing suit comfortably, and are open through the back (although they do create quite an interesting tan line).  The edges of the arm and leg holes of the bathing suit are nicely placed and don't dig while you are wearing the bathing suit.  There is enough material in the crotch area to completely cover everything that needs to be covered, and the neckline also comes up just high enough to cover what needs to be covered there, as well.  While there is a little stretch to the material of the bathing suit, there isn't very much; I think the material is tighter to create a slimmer line on your body.  There is no additional padding or underwire in the bra of the bathing suit.  The listing states to handwash and dry clean; I don't handwash anything, so we washed this in a cold cycle with our regular laundry and then hung it up to dry and didn't have any issues with shrinkage or wearing away of the material.  All of the elastic edging continues to hold firm after several washings.  All of the seams are securely stitched and I didn't notice any loose threads or unravelling seams.  I believe this bathing suit would definitely hold up through several seasons of wearing.

**I received this bathing suit at a discount in exchange for product testing; the above review is a true reflection of my experience with this product and has not been influenced in any way.**
summary: Excellent quality bathing suit, but make sure you buy up a size.

reviewText:
I LOVE the look of this Shmily Sexy Lingerie.  I love the look of the upper lace portion (It looks just as good as the lingerie pieces I have from brand name lingerie makers). What little fabric there is, it is very breathable.  I think it is also the perfect amount of "see-through."
Now on to the fit... I normally wear a size large in lingerie and nightgowns in brands such as Victoria's Secret.  I figured a large would work in this as well, but unfortunately it just doesn't.  I am 5'8 with a long torso, and this style just isn't working on me.  It doesn't cover the areas it is supposed to because it simply doesn't stretch that far.  I even looked to see if I could elongate the straps to make it fit better, but I would also need to extend the length in the middle for it to even work.  I was pretty disappointed it won't work because I really do LOVE how this piece of lingerie looks!
I definitely recommend sizing up if you are a taller girl!

I jus got mine in the mail today and it's perfect! Finally I can show my love for Jolteon with a great pendant! And show love for my team. Team Instinct for the win! I'm so happy I found this! Great colors, great chain, great Pokemon!

This necklace is better quality than I was expecting, and is actually well made. The picture looks exactly the same and it's not glued in in a wonky way as I've seen in this style of pendant before.

The chain is a little longer than I prefer, but it is actually a good one. Sometimes when I buy cheap necklaces online they arrive strung on some tin foil feeling thing that breaks if you look at it wrong, so this was a nice surprise.

The package arrived a lot earlier than estimated, and at the time I'm writing this, Amazon thinks the necklace is still in transit. I ordered this necklace July 21st and it was expected to arrive between August 16th and September 1st. Date received was August 3rd.

I love this necklace, and it was worth the price and shipping cost in my opinion.

Customer service from this company is better than excellent.  We ordered five of these dresses for the bridesmaids in my daughter's wedding.  All of them are in college and on a very tight budget, so we "took our chances" ordering dresses from Amazon rather than a local bridal store.  Each woman customized her dress by submitting her measurements.  We coordinated all orders with the company so all dresses would be made at the same time with the same dye lot fabric.  Felaladress sent a color chart so we could pick our exact fabric color.  They combined all orders, confirmed everything before fabricating the dresses, and all dresses were made and in the mail within a few days.  We received them within a couple weeks from ordering...much quicker than Amazon's estimated delivery date.  All of our emails were promptly answered, often within minutes (during their business hours (America's evening and nighttime hours)).  The quality of these dresses is superb...excellent workmanship, great materials, attention to detail.  No shortcuts.  The bodice and all seams are expertly constructed, lace and beadwork sewn on securely, fantastic quality throughout.  Some of the dresses were too long, but otherwise the fit was very good.  We had a problem with a local seamstress who took up the hem on a couple dresses...they came back smelling like smoke, one had a spot on it, and one had the hem brought up too high.  It was heart breaking. Dry cleaning is very expensive, so I washed them in warm water on delicate in my front loading machine and hung them to dry, and they came out perfect...fresh and clean, as good as new.  The dresses withstood the washing well.  We had to reorder the one that was taken up too much.  Felaladress checked that they still had the same fabrics, confirmed all measurements with me again, and they had the dress in the mail the same day they received the order!  Recommend them and this dress HIGHLY. Be sure to customize your order..it is worth it and you will get exactly what you want.  Really one of the best values for our money that we have ever spent.

reviewText:
This dress is really stunning. I have attached several pictures, but they do not do it justice. Buying dresses online can be complicated, but I used the measuring tool provided and the dress fits pretty much as expected. The only problem I have is that it is pretty long. I am 5'9" tall, and it is very long on me. I ordered a size 12. I normally wear an 8 or 10, but according to the size chart I needed a 12. The back is corseted, so that makes the sizing a little more forgiving. The material is very soft, the beading is beautiful, and I love the neckline as well.
We ordered this dress for my daughter's senior prom. She is more hourglass shaped than I am, but the dress fits her as well as it does me. In the photos attached I have used a tape measure to show the waist, bust, and length measurements. I am standing on the first step of the staircase, so that you can see the entire dress. As you can tell, it is very long. To me, the dress is so beautiful I don't think the additional length warrants taking off a star. As with any formal dress you expect to need alterations. Because of the corseted back the only alteration that will need made is for the length. It fit my daughter and I both despite having completely different body types; we just had to lace the back differently. Overall, I am very pleased with this dress. I am so very glad I bought it.
Disclamer: I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

reviewText: Love the looks.

After wearing a major brand quartz movement watch for many years, I've finally put it away to wear this one instead.  To me, this watch looks dramatically more expensive than it costs, has a large but not-too-large, easy-to-read dial and an elegant metal band that fit my arm perfectly without adjustment.  This watch comes with a link removal tool for those whose arms are smaller.

My past experience with watches that have self-winding, spring-wound movements has been that they have not been as accurate as quartz-regulated, battery powered watches.  This watch has delighted me with its accuracy.  I've been wearing this watch and comparing its accuracy with atomic clock time, and have observed that it has been gaining an average of slightly less than one second a day.  Though still not as accurate as most quartz watches, I found the time-keeping capabilities of this watch to be surprisingly good and certainly good enough for my needs.  I'm more than willing to sacrifice this small difference in accuracy for the handsome appearance of this watch.

Peeking through the transparent window on the back of this watch's case enables me to see the precision movement of this watch in action.  It's a beautiful example of fine workmanship.  For anyone who seeks an expensive watch appearance at a very reasonable price, I can enthusiastically recommend this one, which I received in exchange for an honest evaluation and review.
summary: Accurate and Beautiful Inside and Outside

reviewText:
