Highly recommended for any mom!  I'm still in shock how nice this is for the price.  It's been more durable than the other big brands out there.
This is a really nice charm and my wife loves it.

I love this locket charm. It is so pretty and unique. Not only is it a great Mother's Day gift it is great for saying "I love you mom" any time of the year. The inside of the locket says Best Mom in Purple color letters. The back is engraved with the phrase "I love you". This charm is also a floating charm locket. It opens up. The two sides are kept closed with a pair of magnets on both sides. It makes a pretty secure hold so the little charms inside don't fall out. This comes with 4 little flower shaped floating charms. You can always add more or replace them with different charms. I love all the little cute details on this. All around the front are tiny little shiny Cubic Zirconia crystals. They make this so shiny and sparkly. Hanging from the top is also a little cute heart charm. It has three tiny Purple crystals in the middle. This is a good medium size for a bracelet charm. About 15 X 15 mm in size. The back of the charm is stamped S925 so it is Sterling Silver which I love. All the loops on top are soldered closed. That makes me feel more secure that it won't easily get lost. The charm fit easily onto my Pandora style bracelet. This charm is not very heavy but it does have some weight to it. I found it comfortable to wear but it does tend to hang toward the bottom of the bracelet because of the weight. reviewText:
Just out of curiosity, I bought this along with another one from Choies that had the same identical pictures (Choies was $6 more expensive.) I sized up for both and ordered larges because I knew they ran small. I'm 5'5" and I don't think either would be flattering for anyone who is much taller. There isn't much room lengthwise in the crotch/butt area.

This one has a nude lining whereas Choies has a stark white lining. The lace is pleated under the bust like the picture whereas Choies is not.  In addition Choies is double lined in the chest area so you have the option of wearing without a bra whereas this one is not double lined. The one from Choies is significantly higher quality and made SO better. In comparison to Choies, this was sewn a lot sloppier, the fabric quality was poorer and thinner, and overall just does not seem like it will hold up as well. The end of the one strap was not sewn closed and was fraying along with another portion of the strap. The zipper is in the middle of the back whereas Choies has theirs on the side, but that doesn't make any difference in terms of wearability. However, you can see how much sloppier the zipper was put in compared to Choies. Also there's a lot more loose thread on this one, like on the sides where the lace was serged together.

Like another reviewer mentioned, the right hemline is longer than the left and for me, it was more than two inches longer. This is the biggest reason why I am returning this. Perhaps, not all of them are like that but I cannot keep and wear something this lopsided and uneven. I give this item two stars because it seems unwearable and doesn't seem like it would last, even if it was wearable. At the same time, the item does look like the pictures and would be cute if the hemlines weren't so off.
summary: Uneven Hemline and Sloppier and Poorer Quality Compared to Choies "Identical" Romper

This bracelet is exactly as the photos present it which is a good thing!  The black stones (onyx) are a matte finish rather than polished which I prefer.  However I did fear that the matte finish would be more susceptible to surface scratches or that it might show more wear, but after wearing it daily for a while I haven't noticed that to be a legitimate concern as there are zero scratches on any of the stones.  The blue stone in my bracelet has more color variation than the one in the photos, which is to be expected (because they are natural stones no two will be alike).  My stone is somewhat translucent and I can see the center "cord" inside the stone when viewed at certain angles, while from other angles it is more cloudy and the cord isn't visible.  Personally I prefer the color variation of my stone so I'm glad this isn't just a solid manmade piece of glass.

I have smaller wrists so I was concerned this might be too big for me, but I'm happy to report the sizing is just right.  It is a little loose on my wrist just the way I would want it, but for someone with larger wrists this particular size might be too tight.  For even smaller wrists it would be possible to remove a stone if you were comfortable with cutting and re-tying the center cord but I haven't found the need to do so.  Either way I'd recommend measuring your wrist to ensure this will provide the proper fit.  The other aspect to note is the size of the stones.  They are a bit larger than some of the other options (10mm) each.  I feel like this is the right size for my wrist/hands and it is more of a bulky look than the smaller beads, so although I do agree this might be more of a traditional "men's" size or style, I also feel it would look great on a woman also.  Thus I'd consider this more of a unisex style rather than one just for guys.

Just to note, the center elastic cord is a brown color.  So it really isn't' visible between any of the stones as it blends in, but as I mentioned previously I can see it through the blue stone at certain angles.  Had they used a white cord I suppose it would be less visible through the blue stone, but then I fear I might see little glimpses of white between each of the onyx stones, so it is a tradeoff.  I don't feel the visible cord is really a negative thing but rather a matter of personal preference.

As with my prior AmorWing purchases, it arrived in a very nice gift box which was enclosed in a second box for protection.  This makes it very convenient for gift giving since no further wrapping would be required.  I really have zero complaints about this one - it is exactly what I expected and I like the contrast between the onyx and blue stones.  The bracelet is also very comfortable.  I typically wear a watch but rarely wear other jewelry on my wrists so I wondered if I would be bothered by this... but after a few hours I forgot it was there and I've worn it daily since.  Overall I'm very pleased with this one.  This product was received at a discounted price in exchange for my unbiased review.
summary: Nice Contrast - Unisex Sizing and Style

The crossover style made me think this bra would work for both sleep support and nursing. I was happy about the support and disappointed about the use as a nursing bra.
PRO: It has a comfortable, snug fit and looks nice (not frumpy like other maternity/nursing bras). It has removable padding to help with leaking and provides good support.straps are adjustable for a custom fit.
CON: I didn't find this bra functional for nursing. It is a crossover style like other sleep-style nursing bras. However, the type of straps and lack of elasticity make it impossible to move the cups out of the way. I had to slide the shoulder strap off my shoulder onto my arm to move the cup, trapping my arm to my side. This makes holding a baby or doing anything with your arms very clumsy. I RETURNED the bra for this reason.

reviewText: Great look & fit

It's difficult finding even normal bras in my size (30H). Finding them in a racerback/T back is extra difficult.  Finding a racerback bra in my size that actually looks cute and has cute details, and doesn't cost 80+ bucks?  That's a huge win.  Plus, this company is owned by Chantelle, who make great quality bras, and I believe the quality shows here.  It's comfortable, cute and (in the right size) provides great shape and support.

I don't love everything about this bra.  I actually dislike molded cups, but beggars can't be choosers and I know many women prefer this type of cup.  I would also rather my size be available in more than just black and nude, but that's a typical complaint.  The real issue here is putting the bra on - the adjustable back, which I loved in theory, causes real problems in practice.  Unless you're good at closing your band from behind without help (and I'm not) you'll have to get a little creative.

This Wonbee women's watch came in a beautiful gift box. This watch is absolutely gorgeous and looks elegant on my wrist. The watch is a nice rose gold color and the band is so gorgeous. I love the design of the watch, I love how the crystal stones are position inside of the watch and the 3 extra clocks inside of the watch. The watch has a nice amount of weight to it and doesn't feel heavy on my wrist. The face of the watch is 42 millimeters, and the band is 22 millimeters. The numbers on the  inside of the watch are in Roman numbers, the numbers  on the inside of the 3 other clocks are in regular numbers.  The band on the watch is adjustable, so it can fit most wrist. The watch is Japanese movement, so you know your watch will be carrying accurate time. This watch can be dress up or down and will make your outfit pop. This will make a great gift for family or friend. The price is fair for the quality that you are getting.  I highly recommend this to anybody who is looking for an elegant affordable watch.

I bought these to attend a formal event - one that's very, very important to me. I broke my foot several years ago, and since the doctor didn't set it correctly, it's absolutely ruined. I wanted to wear something with a heel to this event, however, but my dress didn't look good with the big, chunky heels that would have been easier for me to walk on. There's NO way I can wear something like a "kitten heel", even if it's a very, very low one. People gasp when they see how bad my foot is. These heels feel like the wide and chunky ones, but they look sleek. I don't wobble, and I don't feel the pain I feel when I have tried shoes with thin heels that offer no support. They're also very cute, and while they're not the same quality as a 300.00 boot, they are great quality for the price. I'm just so happy to be able to wear heels to this event. I haven't been able to wear them since I injured by foot 12 years ago. I'm very impressed, and I highly recommend these boots.

I've gotten good compliments about it from people, I would say that the price is a bit higher than I'd like to have paid. But for a full frontal design and partial back design it's worth every penny.

The only real problem is that the shirt itself is just a regular t-shirt, meaning that the design will eventually break and fade with printed on shirts. I've had t-shirts with designs embedded within the actual fabric but those cost at least double what this did. For circumstances and situations this will be more than good to show off Polynesian heritage or appreciation.

I was absolutely thrilled for the opportunity to try this bracelet at a reduced price for my sincere opinion.  Immediately on getting this piece home I was in love with it.  On sight I could see that its very well made, the gold tone is beautiful, and I also appreciated the weight of it.  I don't tend to like jewelry that is super light as I would easily lose or break it, so I like things that can stand up to me.  The working cuffs are simply excellent, and really made for a very easy time at getting this bracelet on or off.  As an added plus, the cuffs can even represent an appreciation of an alternative lifestyle.  I am looking forward to adding a small charm or two in order to make this into the gold version of my first medical alert bracelet since I did not like the ones I found that were typically the standard boring ID bracelets.  I feel this bracelet will last, and will definitely serve perfectly for showing my individuality, interests, and even medical alert needs once charmed.  A good buy.
summary: Unique Gorgeous Quality Working Handcuff Bracelet Shares Interests And Can Be Charmed For A Special Medical Alert Piece

reviewText:
My girlfriend loved the color and style of this skirt! The skirt was packaged very nicely and professionally. On the packaging, they offer lots of assistance in the event that something goes wrong with the product which is comforting. The skirt is very versatile. It's very light so you could wear it in the summer, but the texture makes it look somewhat thicker so you could easily use it as a fall/winter skirt and wear tights underneath. With the right sizing, you could dress this skirt up to be very professional as well. The color is very bright and a beautiful royal blue color that works well for all seasons. Overall, it is a great skirt!

Her only complaint was the sizing being off. The waistband is very, very skinny. This style shirt is supposed to be worn higher up so it is usually smaller than your typical hip size. When she tried it on she wore it above the hips as a high waisted skirt and it fit semi-comfortably, but was way too short to wear in public.  Because of the length of the skirt, she tried to wear it on the hips which looked awkward and felt uncomfortably tight. She is a size small and is only 5'3", but this skirt is a bit tight and is way too short. If you are size extra small or small and not very curvy, this skirt would be perfect and I recommend it, but if you are tall or wear sizes bigger than small or are curvy, I don't think this product will fit very well. That being said, the fit is very flattering if you are small or short enough. This skirt appears to give you a very slim, flat stomach, but also shows off curves.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest view and unbiased opinion.

I got this at a discount in exchange for my honest review via amazon review trader.

This skirt is nice for the price.  I ordered this skirt in the blue and it is consistent with the color shown online.  I can't say anything about the other colors, but if the company is consistent throughout, I would expect all colors to be similar as those shown. I usually wear a size 2 or 3 pant and this was a little snug.  No muffin top or anything, but it was definitely tight, and the fabric is fairly stretchy, but the waist band elastic is fairly short.  It is also fairly short, which is saying something for someone who's 5'1" and has an average sized butt - it's not like I have a large butt that needs a lot of fabric to cover.  It's cute and casual.  The waist band is fairly thick, which I like.  I noticed that there is no tag on the product.  Overall, it's not a bad purchase for the price, but be aware that it is short and runs small.  The fabric is also textured, not smooth.  The texture is not well shown on the pictures with the model, but in the close ups of just the skirt, it is.  This is not a problem, just something to note.

This dress looks really good. It's very flattering.

Construction/Quality:
It feels smooth and soft as well. It's not see-through but it's pretty thin. You can see my bra lining through the top. I would probably just wear a little sweater or shrug over it if this bothers you. My hair mostly covers it so I don't mind it myself.  I did move my hair to the side in the pictures so you can see what I mean. There was a bit of loose stitching but nothing really bad. I was able to just snip off the excess. The color is rich. Overall the dress seems well made.

Medium fit:
I'm 5'4" and almost 160lbs and the dress just barely hits the floor without shoes on. I have a newborn and am still working on losing my baby weight which is why I ordered a medium rather than large (hoping to lose the weight soon). Surprisingly the medium still fits well. It has good stretch to it. If you regularly wear medium I think it would still fit but it might be slightly longer than it is on me. I can't wait for spring to be able to wear this regularly. I am all about multi-tasking so it's no surprise that this Convertible Twist Wrap Maxi Beach Dress by Flora Florida intrigued me.  If I can get multiple looks out of one dress then that makes me one happy lady!
If your really creative, or at least more so than me, you could probably come up with even more looks from this one dress.
I love the Nautical look of the blue and white stripes and it looks really cute with beachy sandals and a floppy hat.  However, I would consider this more of a swim suit cover up than an actual dress.  It's made out of 85% Cotton 15% Polyester and it's a little see through so it wouldn't be practical to wear anything but a swimsuit under it.  Which I am totally cool with since I think this makes a great swim suit cover up!
I would also say this dress fit true to size, if anything it maybe runs a little big.  I purchased a Medium and right now I wear about a size 8 to give you some idea of what size you might need to get for yourself.  The fabric is really stretchy and flowy so it's pretty forgiving.
I only gave it 4 stars because it's not really a dress but more of a swimsuit cover up and should be advertised as a cover up.
***I did receive this product at a discount in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.  However, all of my ratings and reviews are my own thoughts and my own opinions and if I don't believe in the product and use it myself then I will not provide a positive review or rating.***

reviewText: Loved the dress, wore it for my baby shower and it was great. Perfect for the occasion.

I love maxi dresses and always looking for some that are not too loud.  Does that make sense?  I am not huge into prints but I love stripes.  This dress is convertible so it is perfect for me.  I was asked to review this product for free or at a discount for my honest review.

Maxi dresses are the best in my opinion.  They can hide a lot on the body, like the baby pouch that didn't go away after having the baby.  Plus the stripes are vertical, so it gives the perception that you are taller and thinner.  Win Win!  All cotton so perfect for warm days but you can absolutely add a sweater.

The top part is two long pieces of fabric that you can tie any way you prefer.  I use a camisole underneath, so I don't show anything I don't want to.  I also plan to use this when I go to the lake.

It is empire cut with an elastic around your ribs.  It isn't too tight, so you don't feel suffocated.  Between the elastic and the top tieing this dress will not be going anywhere it shouldn't.  I recommend this if you are looking for something that is comfortable and can be dressed up or down.
summary: Great Dress for Everyday and Easily Dressed Up.

reviewText:
I'm about 5'3" and a little under 100 lbs.  I bought the extra small, which is my regular size.  I absolutely loved this skirt from the moment I put it on.  It's fairly high-waisted, so no muffin top.  The denim is soft, with almost a brushed feel, and it's quite stretchy.  It goes with lots of different shirts and sweaters, and can be worn in any season.  I think it looks best with high heeled boots or sandals.

It fits like a glove - so much so that I was concerned that if it shrank at all it would be too small.  I washed it in cold water, dried it on extra low and removed it immediately.  Not only did it not shrink, it came out completely free of wrinkles, which made me love it even more.

The reason I rated this skirt four stars instead of five is that it came with the button holes stitched but uncut.  I have no idea what the proper way to cut them might be.  I  ended up just taking a paring knife and poking a hole through the material, widening it a bit, and finishing with scissors.  The first one I did came out messy, and I wish I had started at the bottom button, which would have been less noticeable.  But really, I doubt anyone's going to be looking very closely at my button holes!

All in all, a fantastic skirt for a very good price.

AUGUST 6, 2016
LITTLE "FYI" NOTE ON BUTTON HOLES:

Recently, while shopping for pants, I came across a Chinese seller's warning that the button holes would be uncut.  The reason given was that, in China, uncut button holes indicate that the clothing is new and unworn.  An article of clothing with open button holes would be considered second hand.

So, if you're thinking about purchasing this skirt, it seems the button hole issue may be a result of cultural differences, not shoddy manufacturing.

I'm not adding back a star because I think vendors should adapt to their market.  Items sold in the U.S. are expected to be ready to wear - so either cut the button holes or provide an explanation and directions.
good quality of the product. too small , probably chinese sizing

reviewText: I absolutely would never buy from this outlet again!  The dress that I received and the dress that is seen in the advertisement are distant worlds apart.  It is very cheaply made; it looks like it is freshly off of the sewing table of a beginner just trying their hand at making "stuff," and the material looks like the same material that umberellas are made from.  I was stunned, in a disappointed way, to see what was shipped out parading itself as the beautiful dress in the picture.  In my opinion, it doesn't merit one star, and if you see any stars, I didn't place them in this commentary.  Though it wasn't very expensive, it was originally being sold for $43.+ dollars, still not a boat load of money, but you expect that the quality of the dress would be far better than the poorly constructed misrepresentation that they actually send.  If it hadn' been sent from so far away, I would send it back.  I caution any of you young ladies considering purchasing this dress not to waste your money.  Trust me, my assessment of this dress is neither overstated or unkind, it is simply the naked truth.  SAVE YOUR MONEY!!!  I was really looking forward to the dress in the photo, and received something entirely "else."  What this experience has taught me is that no product coming from an Asian country bought through Amazon, EBay, Stay, etc. can be trusted, this is now the third time that I have been bamboozled purchasing online from stores in an Asian country, I recognize that it's a broad brush that I am painting, and perhaps there are some who send you what is actually being advertised, but that hasn't been my experience; so buyer beware!
summary: False Advertisement; what you see IS NOT what you get.  Buyer, beware!!!

My daughter does run and she felt that it held her in place so that she could run.

The term "sports bra" has a wide range of meanings now and many are designed more for looks than for actual support.  But this one truly justifies the  "High Impact Support" claim.  The first thing my teen said when she tried it on was, "This is a GREAT running bra!"

It's NOT one of the underwire, push-up sports bras. It has a wide, stretchy band and medium-thick pads that can be removed.  Yes, you get the "uni-boob" look,  but that's the price you pay for the kind of support that allows you to do strenuous, active exercise without flopping around.  (Remember Dolly Parton's famous remark that she was afraid to take up jogging for fear one of her bosoms would hit her in the head and cause a concussion?  She could have used one of these.)

What sets this one apart is that the shoulder straps are adjustable,  a feature that we've never seen in a sports bra.  In addition to the "t-back" there's also a back strap with three hooks for getting a better fit.  The straps are lined with the special "wicking" fabric.  The back is porous nylon to prevent sweat build-up.  The hardware is good quality and every seam is neatly double-stitched.  It's a well-made bra.  Ours has been worn and washed (cold water/hung to dry) and we believe it will hold up to use.

I DO think it runs small, but we've gotten used to that problem with on-line clothing purchases and learned to go up a size.  The sizing isn't WAY off, but you should go up a size if you're in doubt.  Again, this is not intended to be a comfy bra to lounge around in, but a support bra for strenuous activity.  If it doesn't fit snugly, it can't do the job.  Keep that in mind when you're considering fit.

This is a great bra for running or strenuous aerobics, especially for those ladies who are more amply endowed and need extra support.  You know who you are.

Free sample provided for review.
summary: A sports bra that means business

reviewText:
I'm a mom to a 21 month old baby girl and in the past 2 years, the number of sports bras I've purchased has been crazy, to say the least. With constant changes needed for size and support, trying to find one that fits, provides great coverage and support, and is also comfortable, has been hard. Also, buying sports bras online isn't the easiest thing to do. But any mom out there knows that online shopping is your best friend when you have a toddler!

I work out 3-4 times a week, consisting of running on the elliptical and then using weight machines and free weights. After two workouts in this bra, I can say it works well for both types of workouts - both for running/cardio and also for using weights. It stays in place as I do different arm movements and such, and also gives adequate support for running. Note that I'm not a high endurance runner or a bodybuilder, so my experience could be different from yours.

Item arrived in cute package, well branded in a plastic bag. Really helped me like the quality of the brand, unlike others which arrived with no special branding in flimsy plastic. Initial inspection showed a good quality material and a well sewn sports bra.

The PROS:
- Smooth, comfortable, fabric
- Breathable
- Wide elastic band that doesn't bunch up
- Supportive padding, not just a flimsy piece of foam
- Adjustable straps

The CONS:
- Wish it came in more colors
- While the straps are adjustable, they aren't the easiest to adjust. I think it is the wide strap, but that is needed I guess for comfort - so not a huge deal breaker for me.

Measurements:
- I purchased a medium size. In the past two years, with being pregnant and breastfeeding, I've been everything between a 32C-34D. At the moment, I'm closer to a 34C and feel like this medium would work for the entire range. So when I have my next baby, I'm glad this bra will work for the duration!

I've tried everything from name brands to discount stores and plenty of online choices as well. I really believe I've found a brand that will work for my lifestyle. I look forward to making more FITTIN purchases.

I received this product at a discount for my unbiased and honest review. I'm in no way inclined to leave a positive review and provide this info so that others can make an informed purchase. I hope you've found it helpful.
summary: Great choice for cardio and free weight workouts

Loved the packing cubes! I have never used them before and tried them for a long vacation.  They kept my clothes organized and I was able to pack ten days worth of clothing in a small carry on, with almost no duplication of outfits.

I received this set as a free review sample. I own a few sets of packing cubes from other brands in various colors and sizes. My observation is that there are premium ones and less quality ones (I own both kinds). This set is definitely premium. One thing that sets premium ones apart is the zippers. Each cube in this set has sturdy zippers that have two pull tabs. They are not prone to coming off the tracks like the lower quality cubes. Another thing is the stitching, which on these is close and straight. Note that the stitching is on the inside of the cubes, and along hem lines. A feature that I especially like is there are handles across the tops of each cube. To be honest, for their intended purpose I am not sure how useful their are, but for the way I use these cubes they are a nice feature. I organize and store cables and other odds and ends in all of the cube sets that I own. The open mesh allows me to see at a glance if a particular cube has instrument, microphone or speaker cables, or small electronic gizmos that I use on stage. And the construction of these cubes are why I rated them so highly, because cables in the larger cube weigh in at close to eight pounds. This particular brand is sturdy enough to hold them without splitting like lesser cubes are apt to do. Finally, for folks who are actually using these for their intended purpose, they are labeled with a graphic of what each cube is designed to hold: outer wear, underwear and the such. Not that it needs those since the open mesh reveals what is actually inside, but I thought it was a nice touch displaying attention to detail. If you are a traveler these will allow you to pack neatly and actually maximize space in carry-on baggage. If you are a camper or just need bags to organize gear this set is excellent. If you are a musician, this is perfect for organizing cables. I actually use an On Stage KSB6500 Keyboard Stand Bag to hold cubes with specific cable types, and the arrangement works perfectly.
summary: Very well made with high quality zippers

reviewText:
This is a fantastic product! I was a little doubtful at first, because it looks very plasticy and cheap in the pictures, but I was pleasantly surprised at the overall quality of manufacture. It's true that the material is quite thin, but it's actually fairly sturdy (or so I assume, because I tend to be quite rough on my clothing, and it hasn't torn at all). The lacing well places and contours well, and the ribbing is a sturdy-yet-flexible plastic that allows this corset to shape correctly for just about any body (I'm very flat-chested, and fairly skinny, which is a body-type that doesn't fit most corsets well). The neck-strap at the top is very sexy and works well, although it took me a minute to figure out how to fold the collar when I first got the corset. Be aware, though, that the back-less design ends up putting a lot of pressure on your neck, so if you have any pre-existing neck issues, you'll want to wear the neck-strap extra loose. The clasps on the front are all steel posts-and-hooks connected to sturdy steel ribbing on each side. I *am* slightly concerned that the steel front-ribs will eventually pierce through the thin material, but so far so good. WARNING: the front ribs are long, and not very flexible, making it harder than normal to sit down in this corset. Even sitting straight up, the ribs will press into the material and risk tearing if you sit for too long.

My only major issue so far is that the top post from the front clasp broke away and went missing after only three uses of the corset. However, the large number of clasps and strong steel boning of the clasp means that I haven't noticed any adverse effect from having lost that top post. I'm going to request a replacement, due to this defect, but so far I haven't seen any detriment.

Overall, I am thrilled with this product!
summary: Great Corset for Any Body Type.

Maybe I just got lucky? I should be able to sew it/ take it in a little myself so it'll fit perfectly before the event I bought this for occurs. Now, MATERIALS- Ok, NOT REAL LEATHER. I didn't expect genuine leather for $40, so no surprise there. The fabric (?) feels heavy but cheap & probably couldn't stand up to too rough of wear/tear, but again, what did I expect for $40, shipping from China? Again, it'll work great for wearing to kink events= good enough for me! It IS difficult to maneuver opening or closing the front, but that part Does seem sturdily made!  Finals thoughts- great for $40, would NOT be good if it actually had to cinch me into a shape other than I am, Definitely looks hot! I ordered Feb 6, it arrived via USPS Feb 23, Long before the anticipated delivery date of Mar 6-23.

reviewText: I have a granddaughter who loves anything "Nightmare Before Christmas". The necklace is high quality and she will love it.

This necklace is a lovely piece of costume jewelry. I've always been a fan of Nightmare Before Christmas, but this is the first time I've seen Jack and Sally on jewelry.  The pendant is silvertone with some antiquing.  The necklace is surprisingly lightweight for as large as it is.  The moon has swirls and the center dangle has a bumpy texture.  There are many designs to choose from, but I chose the black and yellow.  I've already received compliments on this necklace.  The only drawback is the center pendant slips behind the moon a little bit. I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

My husband and I try to take my kids to Disneyland every year.  If you have been to Disneyland you know how caught up you get into wanting to wear everything Disney.  A few years ago I clicked.  Buy the cool items on Amazon for a fraction of the cost in Disneyland!

While The Nightmare Before Christmas was not a favorite of my kids (too scary), I still absolutely love Jack Skellington and Sally.  I just couldn't resist this necklace!  I was really blown away at the variety this necklace comes in.  There are so many choices and scenes to choose from.  I chose blue white because I feel it really represents the essence of the movie.

I was delighted to see the necklace when it arrived.  The colors are so vibrant and bold.  The scene really stands out.  The picture is within a glass pendant and looks very elegant.  I love the silver moon that surrounds the glass pendant.  The clasp is nice and secure and the chain is very pretty.  The piece has such an interesting look to it, and I cant wait to show it off!

I received this item at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.
summary: Super Cute Jack Skellington and Sally Necklace from Nightmare Before Christmas

reviewText:
I am reviewing this item purely by visuals and not with any actual knowledge of whether these beads are really semi-precious agate and tiger eye. My initial impression of this 12mm dragon bead bracelet is that there was a good heft to it. The beads have a solidity that gives the impression that these beads are the real thing. But because Im neither a jeweler nor a gemstone expert, Im not certain these are really what they are advertised as.

What I can say, however, is that this bead bracelet by fourlady looks to be of good quality. There are no discrepancies on any of the beads and the shine on the beads look very natural. The four red tinted beads have a nice effect very much like what tiger eye stones should look like, and they all have a different natural pattern.

The center bead of the bracelet is a dragon etched bead that is slightly larger than the rest of the beads. The silver figure is etched directly on the bead and not painted on, which is nice as it means the pattern will last longer. You can depict a serpentine eastern-style dragon on the bead although it took me a while to find the head and the ends of the tail. The dragon on my bead looks different from the dragon on the listing photo which means each of these beads are hand etched and not one of them are exactly the same as the other, which is a nice thought.

I believe the quality of this bead bracelet is very nice and implies authenticity although I have no 100% way to be sure unless I take this directly to an expert to investigate. However, for the inexpensive price, I would say that the bead bracelet is well worth the price due to the feel and heft of the bracelet. The diameter of the bracelet is 12mm, which is slightly large on the average womens wrist, but this is the right size for a male wrist. Still, the bracelet does have a unisex design with a nice color combination. Black and red always look great together.

This would make a great present to those fashion-conscious friends of yours, both men and women. The elastic that holds the beads together seem to be relatively durable and gives some leeway in terms of wrist size. I received a sample of this dragon bead bracelet for testing and use and this is my honest and unbiased review.
summary: Good heft to a nice bracelet for an inexpensive price.

Also one of the other reviewers had mentioned the round bra inserts that look like coconut halves.  I discovered that those are removable through a small slot at the bottom underarm area.  I took those inserts out and tried it on with my regular under wire bra and it looks great and the bra doesn't show at all it's completely covered. reviewText:
I am brand new to wearing sleep masks.  I've been trying everything I can think of to stop the dry eye effects of the surgeries I've had to undergo to my lower left eyelid.  These surgeries resulted in losing most of the lower outside corner of my bottom eyelid, leaving more of my eye exposed and making that eye remain partially open as I sleep.

My granddaughter gave me the bright idea of the sleep mask, but I couldn't decide which type to get.  So I purchased this YUEDGE contoured mask and the Alaska Bear traditional style satin sleep mask with dual straps. I tried this YUEDGE first and liked it very much - except there is no adjusting the back strap.  I fall asleep on my side every night but switch back and forth to my back through the night, and the lack of ability to tighten this mask was the only complaint I could come up with.

I love that my eyelids aren't touched by the mask.  It makes wearing it almost weightless, and it did help some with preventing the air from drying out my eye.  However, it wasn't 5-star perfect because I couldn't get a solid seal by tightening that strip...

...until I used both masks together.  :-D

So glad I purchased both - the adjustable dual-strap traditional mask over this contoured mask fit the bill perfectly.

A word for those concerned with the dye discoloring your bedclothes.  Soak your sleep mask in vinegar water and wash by hand after a couple of hours. Then hang to dry.  The vinegar helps set the dye so it won't run.
This mask is okay but bleeds like crazy. My pillow case has black stains on it. Suggest washing it first before using to wash off the dye.

I bought the black hooded version of this jacket; it is a really cool and stylish design and I love it. To give some idea about sizing, I am 5'9" and fairly thin, and I normally wear medium-sized clothes. For this jacket, I ordered one size larger, the US large (Asian XXL), because some people have stated that the jacket runs small. I also compared my own measurements to the ones on the jacket's sizing chart, and saw that the large was probably the the most appropriate size for me. The jacket fits me well and the sleeves are just the right length.

The jacket has a detachable hood, three outer pockets, an ornamental vertical zipper on the right breast, and one inside pocket. The two lower pockets have smaller pockets on top of them which I guess would be useful for sticking your hands in when you're cold; the openings are on the sides so items would probably fall out.  The inside lining is really smooth and comfortable, and the overall construction seems well done and durable.

A minor but interesting note: There's some pretty amusing Engrish text embossed on the buttons. On my jacket, most of the buttons read "CLASSIC", but the one the left cuff reads "PHYSICAL PLAYBOY". As a bonus, the rivets on the lower pockets, which are smaller than the buttons, read "HYSICAL LAYBOY" due to a lack of space. I personally find stuff like that really funny, so it actually makes me love the jacket even more, and it doesn't detract from its appearance at all.

Overall, this is the coolest jacket I've ever owned and I look forward to wearing it a lot.
summary: Very cool and stylish jacket; pay attention to sizing though

I bought the dress with the white background. Here are things you should know before buying:**

1) If you are between sizes go up a size.
2) The print with the white background is slightly see-through
3) The material feels like a textured polyester-- there is an actual zigzag texture to it, not just the print. It is also a little itchy.
4) The collar and the back insert look like they were attached to change the original style-- the added pieces are VERY obvious and, though they do add a touch of modesty, it would have been cuter without them since they are added in a piecemeal way. (See 5)
5) No attention to the pattern is paid when cutting the pieces, so your dress might have a big flower over one breast and not on the other creating a lopsided appearance.
6) This dress looks like it will be a swing skirt in the photos, but it is not. There are large pleats all around the waistline, rather than a circle skirt or a-line, that creates fullness at the waist.
7) It smelled strongly of chemicals when it arrived.

**The sellers have since contacted me and offered a partial refund. I had already returned the item for all the reasons above, but they asked that I changed my rating so I wouldn't affect their overall rating. I won't change my rating as it is based on the product, not the seller. The seller seems willing to work with customers, but I still can't recommend this particular product, BUT I would be willing to try other products from this vendor.

I believe the most value I can provide in a review will be through pictures, so I've attached some images of how the dress looks on my body. For reference, I usually wear a size 10. Here are some thoughts I have about the dress:

Fit:
Fits tight. As other reviewers have mentioned, that means the dress will show every imperfection. I think it's therefore best-suited for people smaller than I am, but I think it looked decent on me (and will therefore look decent on other people of my size.)

Appearance:
The color has a nice hue. Some of the ruching is nice, while in other areas it looks a bit like wrinkles (see in pictures.) I LOVE the little cape thing!! It's the detail that drew me to the dress.

Comfort:
As long as you're comfortable with how the dress looks on you, you should be comfortable in this dress. The fabric feels nice and the dress is long enough that you don't need to worry about flashing anyone.

Overall, I think this is a great dress with some small flaws and it should work well for most people.

reviewText:
I used to have a friend that always said this look was created by using leg warmers but their such a popular style in so many anime and manga's that i just didn't think that was true. But i spent a very long time searching and finally i actually found some!

So to start, my friend was actually closer to the truth than not. They really are a lot like basic socks with the leg warmers attached but i was impressed with the weight of them. They aren't the light weight cheap cotton like you would find at your local Walmart. They are actually a surprising  heavy cotton but with the way its constructed, they actually breath pretty well too which makes these a pretty versatile product. Honestly I wonder why they have never been marketed in the US. Depending on the length of the pair you can scrunch them down pretty far so your not covering your legs to much but if it starts to get to chilli you can pull them WAY up, the longer versions can easily go all the way to the top of your thighs even if you happen to be a bit taller than average their should still be more than enough material for that. That said, they're not very practical for use with anything other than a skirt or dress simply because of the amount of material they have. For example if you tried wearing them with a pair of pants you'd probably just end up with a huge bulge at the bottom of your pants leg or it would look like you were trying to wear sweat pants under your pants. Still, I do really like them and would love to get a few more pairs but the high price makes it hard to justify getting more than the ones I already have.

I got the 180cm socks. They are definitely long. The knit is bulky as pictured, and the socks are accurately colored [as pictured]. it's more of a warm white than a bright white [more like the color of milk, I guess] but they are definitely still white and I can't wait to wear them with some of my planned fall kogal outfits.

I measured these and they are definitely as advertised. They also fit my size 11 [woman's] feet perfectly fine due to the stretchy nature of the sock.
